1
00:00:05,801 --> 00:00:07,361
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,431 --> 00:00:09,171
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,401 --> 00:00:11,631
(Episode 43)

4
00:00:30,451 --> 00:00:32,261
- Mom.
- Mom.

5
00:00:33,191 --> 00:00:37,791
Isn't that Jo Mi Hyang?
That crazy woman...

6
00:00:38,531 --> 00:00:39,531
- Jeong Han!
- Hey!

7
00:00:39,601 --> 00:00:41,961
- Mom, are you okay? Mom.
- Hey. Stop right there. Hey, you...

8
00:00:42,631 --> 00:00:46,071
That's eight, 80, 87...
Gosh, seriously.

9
00:00:46,141 --> 00:00:48,911
Jeong Han. Mom, are you okay?

10
00:00:48,971 --> 00:00:51,911
- Mom, are you okay?
- Mom, hold still.

11
00:00:51,971 --> 00:00:53,441
- Oh, Mom.
- I'm calling 911.

12
00:00:53,781 --> 00:00:57,451
No, I'm fine.
Goodness, I was just so startled.

13
00:00:57,551 --> 00:01:00,981
Mom, let's get you home first. Okay?

14
00:01:01,221 --> 00:01:02,391
Are you okay, Mom?

15
00:01:02,651 --> 00:01:04,621
(Gong Gi Cheol, Gong Gi Cheol.
I Am Gong Gi Cheol)

16
00:01:06,461 --> 00:01:07,461
Father.

17
00:01:07,891 --> 00:01:08,891
Yes.

18
00:01:12,361 --> 00:01:14,161
- Father.
- Yes?

19
00:01:14,231 --> 00:01:16,831
Shall we do our card therapy today?

20
00:01:17,631 --> 00:01:18,801
Let's do that.

21
00:01:19,571 --> 00:01:21,871
Then I'll get it ready
and let you know.

22
00:01:22,141 --> 00:01:23,871
Honey. Honey.

23
00:01:28,341 --> 00:01:31,081
Mom, careful, careful. Okay?

24
00:01:31,081 --> 00:01:33,781
Wait. Mom, what happened?

25
00:01:33,851 --> 00:01:36,951
Dae Han. Here. Help Mom lie down
in her room. Okay?

26
00:01:36,991 --> 00:01:39,361
- Okay. Careful, Mom.
- What in the world...

27
00:01:40,421 --> 00:01:42,531
Honey, what happened?

28
00:01:43,461 --> 00:01:47,561
Jo Mi Hyang tried to run over Mom
with her car.

29
00:01:47,631 --> 00:01:49,201
- Jo Mi Hyang?
- What?

30
00:01:49,271 --> 00:01:52,601
Yes. It looks like she was hiding
and waiting near the house.

31
00:01:53,171 --> 00:01:57,871
- Is she hurt?
- No. It was a very close call.

32
00:02:03,851 --> 00:02:04,851
Mother...

33
00:02:12,091 --> 00:02:13,091
Unbelievable.

34
00:02:50,091 --> 00:02:52,831
If she was lying in wait
with intent to harm,

35
00:02:53,061 --> 00:02:55,831
this case could warrant
an attempted murder charge.

36
00:02:57,231 --> 00:03:01,041
For now, for her protection,
at Ms. Na's home and the pharmacy,

37
00:03:01,101 --> 00:03:03,511
we will increase patrols
throughout the market area.

38
00:03:03,711 --> 00:03:06,111
Why on earth would she do that?

39
00:03:06,711 --> 00:03:09,611
Actually, this morning, my father...

40
00:03:10,151 --> 00:03:14,251
- recovered some of his memories.
- Oh, really?

41
00:03:15,321 --> 00:03:16,651
Thirty years ago,

42
00:03:17,491 --> 00:03:18,991
Jo Mi Hyang hit my father,

43
00:03:19,621 --> 00:03:22,831
on the head with a rock.
That's what he said.

44
00:03:23,131 --> 00:03:27,661
- What?
- So he lost his memory from that...

45
00:03:27,731 --> 00:03:31,431
Yes. Also, my father...

46
00:03:31,801 --> 00:03:34,841
said that he's never killed anyone.

47
00:03:36,011 --> 00:03:39,681
It seems connected to the death
of Jo Mun Sik.

48
00:03:39,981 --> 00:03:42,041
Still, it's a relief
that his memory...

49
00:03:42,111 --> 00:03:43,111
is starting to return.

50
00:03:43,311 --> 00:03:46,651
His testimony could be vital
in solving this case.

51
00:03:46,951 --> 00:03:50,521
I'll report this to the station to
proceed with further investigation.

52
00:03:50,651 --> 00:03:54,061
We'll also track
Jo Mi Hyang's vehicle.

53
00:03:54,261 --> 00:03:56,661
In the meantime,
everyone please be careful.

54
00:03:57,731 --> 00:04:00,801
- Yes. Thank you.
- Right.

55
00:04:14,341 --> 00:04:15,881
Yes, thank you.

56
00:04:22,321 --> 00:04:23,791
What's with the good manners?

57
00:04:24,491 --> 00:04:27,161
- Gosh.
- As if. There's no way.

58
00:04:27,221 --> 00:04:29,791
You drive.
I barely slept last night.

59
00:04:29,861 --> 00:04:34,031
Me neither. Let's settle it
with rock-paper-scissors...

60
00:04:38,701 --> 00:04:40,801
Gosh, so obnoxious.

61
00:05:03,361 --> 00:05:05,331
Seriously.

62
00:05:05,431 --> 00:05:08,361
Who has the nerve to snore away
in the passenger seat?

63
00:05:08,661 --> 00:05:10,071
Is this your idea of revenge?

64
00:05:10,131 --> 00:05:12,131
No. Your shift was overdue
by 35 minutes,

65
00:05:12,201 --> 00:05:13,641
so I took appropriate action.

66
00:05:13,701 --> 00:05:16,311
Wow, you actually sat there
and timed me.

67
00:05:16,811 --> 00:05:20,381
Oh, wait, wait. Turn around
at the next intersection.

68
00:05:20,541 --> 00:05:21,541
Why?

69
00:05:22,181 --> 00:05:25,111
There's an amazing pork loin
cutlet place near here.

70
00:05:25,181 --> 00:05:27,381
Let's have lunch there
and then switch.

71
00:05:28,121 --> 00:05:30,621
We're in a hurry,
and all you want to do...

72
00:05:30,691 --> 00:05:32,661
is go on a food tour. Seriously.

73
00:05:33,161 --> 00:05:35,521
It's from that variety show,
"Three Days and Two Nights."

74
00:05:35,591 --> 00:05:36,591
You know it, right?

75
00:05:36,761 --> 00:05:39,531
It's the place that was featured
on Season Two, Episode 49.

76
00:05:42,731 --> 00:05:47,101
It serves a modern take
on the classic, Western-style pork cutlet.

77
00:05:48,501 --> 00:05:50,071
Their special demi-glace sauce,

78
00:05:50,141 --> 00:05:52,641
it has the balance of acidity,
sweetness, and umami.

79
00:05:52,711 --> 00:05:54,611
They say it's a masterpiece.

80
00:05:55,581 --> 00:05:56,581
Too late, I said it all.

81
00:06:00,281 --> 00:06:01,521
Unbelievable.

82
00:06:18,601 --> 00:06:21,741
Don't cut it all at once.
Just eat it one piece at a time.

83
00:06:22,141 --> 00:06:23,711
I'll eat it how I want.
What do you care?

84
00:06:23,811 --> 00:06:25,441
But that way, it stays juicy.

85
00:06:25,511 --> 00:06:27,681
Okay? You have to eat it
while it's crispy and warm...

86
00:06:27,741 --> 00:06:29,781
I'll eat it how I want.
What do you care?

87
00:06:37,591 --> 00:06:39,421
Were our tastes
always this different?

88
00:06:39,891 --> 00:06:41,921
Tell me about it.
I have no idea why I thought...

89
00:06:41,991 --> 00:06:43,861
we were so compatible
when we were dating.

90
00:06:44,191 --> 00:06:47,531
I guess love is blind.
Our judgment must've been clouded.

91
00:06:48,361 --> 00:06:51,271
Well, I'm glad we've finally
come to our senses.

92
00:07:05,611 --> 00:07:08,981
What was that? Was that thunder?

93
00:07:09,151 --> 00:07:11,091
Was there rain
in the forecast today?

94
00:07:12,961 --> 00:07:15,021
What's wrong? Are you sick?

95
00:07:15,791 --> 00:07:18,061
- The restroom.
- What?

96
00:07:18,131 --> 00:07:19,561
I need to use the restroom.

97
00:07:19,931 --> 00:07:21,061
All right.

98
00:07:24,501 --> 00:07:26,171
- Step on it.
- What?

99
00:07:26,241 --> 00:07:27,241
I said step on it.

100
00:07:27,571 --> 00:07:28,571
Okay.

101
00:07:29,071 --> 00:07:30,271
Then put some spit on your nose.

102
00:07:31,171 --> 00:07:33,341
That's for when
your foot falls asleep.

103
00:07:33,981 --> 00:07:38,281
Okay, then try a mantra.
"I'm fine. I won't go."

104
00:07:38,351 --> 00:07:40,921
"I absolutely won't go."

105
00:07:41,381 --> 00:07:42,381
Hey!

106
00:07:43,551 --> 00:07:44,851
Okay, okay.

107
00:07:47,691 --> 00:07:51,531
(Weigh Station)

108
00:07:55,971 --> 00:07:58,671
- Hey, here. Take this toilet paper.
- They'll have some in there.

109
00:07:58,731 --> 00:08:00,171
What if they don't?
This is better...

110
00:08:00,241 --> 00:08:02,041
than you yelling for me
to bring you some.

111
00:08:06,811 --> 00:08:10,051
Hurry up! Go, go!

112
00:08:22,291 --> 00:08:25,231
What's the big deal?
It's not like we're dating.

113
00:08:28,561 --> 00:08:30,671
It's just a natural bodily function.

114
00:08:31,101 --> 00:08:32,101
You think this is funny?

115
00:08:32,371 --> 00:08:33,371
Is it that obvious?

116
00:08:35,241 --> 00:08:37,641
Why did you have to suggest
we get pork cutlet?

117
00:08:37,711 --> 00:08:40,041
Hey, it's not
the pork cutlet's fault.

118
00:08:40,111 --> 00:08:41,981
Look at me. I'm perfectly fine.

119
00:08:42,111 --> 00:08:44,651
You're so unbelievably annoying.

120
00:08:46,381 --> 00:08:47,921
Wait a minute.

121
00:08:49,191 --> 00:08:50,821
What's that smell?

122
00:08:52,661 --> 00:08:54,421
What do you mean, what's that smell?

123
00:08:58,861 --> 00:09:00,761
It's not me.

124
00:09:01,361 --> 00:09:02,601
Seriously.

125
00:09:03,301 --> 00:09:06,301
I said it's not me. Seriously.

126
00:09:16,781 --> 00:09:20,751
Se Ri. I'm ready. Let's go.

127
00:09:21,651 --> 00:09:23,651
A date? Where are you going?

128
00:09:23,721 --> 00:09:26,891
Oh, I have a round of golf
with Councilor Hwang tomorrow,

129
00:09:26,891 --> 00:09:28,061
so I'm buying some clothes.

130
00:09:28,521 --> 00:09:30,061
What's the occasion?

131
00:09:30,561 --> 00:09:32,961
Why is everyone suddenly
so diligent about drinking water?

132
00:09:33,261 --> 00:09:35,031
You should drink more water
too, honey.

133
00:09:35,201 --> 00:09:37,431
The older you get, the more you have
to take care of the basics.

134
00:09:37,771 --> 00:09:39,571
I'm going to use this
alkaline ionizer...

135
00:09:39,641 --> 00:09:43,211
- to take care of family's health.
- I should drink more too.

136
00:09:43,911 --> 00:09:47,081
- Here you go. This is for you.
- Thanks, Se Ri.

137
00:09:47,341 --> 00:09:49,481
It's reassuring to have you
looking out for me.

138
00:09:49,551 --> 00:09:51,151
I'll carry this around and drink it.

139
00:09:51,811 --> 00:09:52,981
Eun Bin, want to come with us?

140
00:09:53,081 --> 00:09:57,121
Oh, I'm good.
You two have a nice date.

141
00:09:57,551 --> 00:09:59,051
We wouldn't take you
even if you wanted to come.

142
00:10:02,021 --> 00:10:03,991
- Let's go, honey.
- Okay.

143
00:10:04,291 --> 00:10:07,661
- Which one do you think is best?
- Honey, for this round of golf,

144
00:10:07,731 --> 00:10:09,671
I was thinking of
wearing a brighter color.

145
00:10:09,731 --> 00:10:11,231
Maybe I can really stand out?

146
00:10:11,301 --> 00:10:15,971
But honey, you stand out
even when you do nothing.

147
00:10:16,341 --> 00:10:17,511
So do you.

148
00:10:19,511 --> 00:10:21,911
Honey, what about this?

149
00:10:21,981 --> 00:10:24,981
Wow, that's great. That's my
girl's fashion sense for you.

150
00:10:25,581 --> 00:10:27,521
Let's pick out some clothes
for you, too.

151
00:10:27,581 --> 00:10:29,121
Enough to fill your whole closet.

152
00:10:29,321 --> 00:10:31,951
- Oh, I'm fine.
- What are you talking about?

153
00:10:32,961 --> 00:10:36,091
Dr. Han Seong Mi prescribed
shopping, remember?

154
00:10:36,331 --> 00:10:40,331
This is a medically necessary splurge.
Got it? Pick out a ton.

155
00:10:40,731 --> 00:10:42,801
Well, maybe I'll pick out
a few things then?

156
00:10:43,071 --> 00:10:44,101
Deal.

157
00:10:44,931 --> 00:10:47,671
- Can I help you?
- Could you give us recommendations?

158
00:10:47,741 --> 00:10:48,741
Of course.

159
00:10:50,711 --> 00:10:54,981
- How about this one?
- Oh, it's nice. I like it.

160
00:10:55,881 --> 00:10:58,751
She's the most beautiful wife
in the world, you know.

161
00:10:58,981 --> 00:11:01,081
Honey, don't hesitate.
Just get them all.

162
00:11:01,481 --> 00:11:02,851
- Oh, my.
- Right.

163
00:11:03,521 --> 00:11:04,621
Because you're my girl.

164
00:11:04,951 --> 00:11:07,661
- Oh my, what is all this?
- Yes. Just buy it all.

165
00:11:20,901 --> 00:11:21,901
Eun Bin!

166
00:11:23,311 --> 00:11:24,471
- Woo Jae.
- Are you okay?

167
00:11:27,381 --> 00:11:29,981
Hey, what's your problem?
What do you think you're doing?

168
00:11:31,181 --> 00:11:34,821
We're not even dating.
Why's he being so cool?

169
00:11:39,621 --> 00:11:41,761
Oh, it's fine.
There's a convenience store.

170
00:11:41,761 --> 00:11:42,991
I can just buy some slippers.

171
00:11:43,431 --> 00:11:44,661
Want a piggyback,
or do you want to wear these?

172
00:11:46,401 --> 00:11:48,201
"Want a piggyback,
or do you want to wear these?"

173
00:11:49,431 --> 00:11:53,241
We're not even dating.
Why is he being so sweet?

174
00:11:58,041 --> 00:11:59,941
Oh, it's Woo Jae.

175
00:12:02,911 --> 00:12:04,451
Yes, in-law?

176
00:12:05,151 --> 00:12:06,681
Eun Bin, you have a resume, right?

177
00:12:07,181 --> 00:12:08,321
A resume?

178
00:12:08,721 --> 00:12:09,851
I don't have one.

179
00:12:09,851 --> 00:12:11,921
You don't even have a resume
when you're job hunting?

180
00:12:12,991 --> 00:12:14,891
I was just about to make one.

181
00:12:15,561 --> 00:12:16,761
Come out now. We're making one.

182
00:12:17,731 --> 00:12:19,831
Come out? Where to?

183
00:12:24,171 --> 00:12:27,141
You scared me.
When did you get here?

184
00:12:27,671 --> 00:12:28,671
Just now.

185
00:12:28,741 --> 00:12:32,671
If you were here,
you should've knocked. Why call?

186
00:12:33,511 --> 00:12:35,181
Let's go. Get changed and come down.

187
00:12:35,611 --> 00:12:36,981
Where are we going?

188
00:12:39,421 --> 00:12:42,791
We're not even dating.
Why's he acting so tough?

189
00:12:43,491 --> 00:12:44,991
"Get changed and come down."

190
00:12:52,131 --> 00:12:53,561
Just a second.

191
00:12:57,131 --> 00:12:58,571
Just move your hair
a little like this...

192
00:13:00,771 --> 00:13:01,801
Hold on.

193
00:13:05,741 --> 00:13:07,441
There. Just relax.

194
00:13:08,681 --> 00:13:10,351
- Okay, she's ready.
- Taking the shot.

195
00:13:10,411 --> 00:13:11,411
Okay.

196
00:13:15,621 --> 00:13:16,991
Okay, looks good.

197
00:13:28,331 --> 00:13:29,531
Okay, looks good.

198
00:13:32,001 --> 00:13:33,001
Done.

199
00:13:35,541 --> 00:13:36,541
What do you think?

200
00:13:38,711 --> 00:13:40,381
(Ojin High School, Dobuk University,
Social Welfare)

201
00:13:40,441 --> 00:13:42,611
It's a resume
without any experience.

202
00:13:43,251 --> 00:13:44,651
I'll fill it up as I go.

203
00:13:45,981 --> 00:13:48,081
Well, I like your optimism.

204
00:13:51,721 --> 00:13:53,191
(Film, Stylist Wanted,
Experience Required)

205
00:13:53,261 --> 00:13:55,221
Are there any I can apply for?

206
00:13:55,561 --> 00:13:58,061
Almost all the stylist jobs
require experience.

207
00:13:59,261 --> 00:14:00,431
Right?

208
00:14:01,331 --> 00:14:02,701
Entry-level applicants welcome.

209
00:14:03,231 --> 00:14:05,101
- Where, where?
- Right here.

210
00:14:06,071 --> 00:14:08,901
I'm going to apply for this one.

211
00:14:09,541 --> 00:14:11,471
Being a stylist is
an all-day job, you know.

212
00:14:11,471 --> 00:14:13,411
Are you okay with that?

213
00:14:13,611 --> 00:14:14,911
Of course.

214
00:14:16,381 --> 00:14:20,081
But it says to submit a portfolio.

215
00:14:20,421 --> 00:14:22,991
What's that? Is there anything
I can do to help?

216
00:14:24,951 --> 00:14:27,521
There is. Are you busy tomorrow?

217
00:14:28,721 --> 00:14:29,731
No.

218
00:14:32,931 --> 00:14:34,831
What do we do now?

219
00:14:36,001 --> 00:14:39,601
You should have begged him to
stay on until our brand launch.

220
00:14:41,201 --> 00:14:44,771
He said he's retiring and plans
to move to the country for good.

221
00:14:45,211 --> 00:14:48,441
He seemed uncomfortable that
we showed up without an appointment.

222
00:14:49,481 --> 00:14:51,611
We should have been more careful
in our approach...

223
00:14:52,851 --> 00:14:54,981
Look who's talking. You're the one
who failed to persuade him.

224
00:14:55,151 --> 00:14:57,891
Isn't reading people and persuading
them your specialty, Director Yang?

225
00:14:58,321 --> 00:15:00,591
Seriously, why did you even come?
You only drove half the way.

226
00:15:00,821 --> 00:15:04,591
All right, stop fighting
and please focus on the sample work.

227
00:15:04,661 --> 00:15:05,661
Sorry.

228
00:15:05,961 --> 00:15:09,361
Just in case, I made a list
of sample rooms with good quality.

229
00:15:10,901 --> 00:15:12,631
Should we split the list
and start calling?

230
00:15:14,241 --> 00:15:15,301
Calling them won't be enough.

231
00:15:18,271 --> 00:15:19,271
You're not coming?

232
00:15:19,681 --> 00:15:20,681
I am.

233
00:15:27,681 --> 00:15:29,321
- Keep it up.
- Right.

234
00:15:36,891 --> 00:15:38,731
I'm begging you, ma'am.

235
00:15:39,231 --> 00:15:42,101
I'm telling you, we can't even
handle the orders we already have.

236
00:15:42,431 --> 00:15:45,971
But couldn't you please
just do two styles for us?

237
00:15:46,271 --> 00:15:49,001
We'll do our best to meet your price
for the labor costs.

238
00:15:50,211 --> 00:15:51,771
To be honest,

239
00:15:52,041 --> 00:15:54,511
we're hesitant to work
with a new brand.

240
00:15:55,611 --> 00:15:57,751
Please look for someone else.
I'm sorry.

241
00:16:04,321 --> 00:16:05,791
(Unique Workroom)

242
00:16:05,851 --> 00:16:09,761
Wow, without the Taehan name
backing me, I'm really nothing.

243
00:16:10,531 --> 00:16:14,061
There's only one place left,
what will I do if they say no too?

244
00:16:15,031 --> 00:16:18,801
Hey, stop being so negative.
You're going to jinx us.

245
00:16:19,171 --> 00:16:21,201
I'm just being realistic.

246
00:16:22,001 --> 00:16:23,011
Just you watch.

247
00:16:23,541 --> 00:16:26,041
I won't let any crisis get me down,

248
00:16:26,271 --> 00:16:29,441
and I will overcome this.
Pacu Nacho...

249
00:16:30,781 --> 00:16:32,181
Gosh, seriously.

250
00:16:36,791 --> 00:16:38,251
How are you feeling, Mother?

251
00:16:40,291 --> 00:16:42,191
I'll be fine if I get some rest.

252
00:16:44,031 --> 00:16:47,601
Nothing happened with that woman,
did it?

253
00:16:49,061 --> 00:16:52,171
I don't know.
I can't remember anything.

254
00:16:53,241 --> 00:16:56,411
What could we have possibly done
for her to do this to us?

255
00:17:02,981 --> 00:17:05,751
(Anxious, Baffled, Resentful)

256
00:17:05,811 --> 00:17:08,251
Father, you've been suppressing
your emotions...

257
00:17:08,321 --> 00:17:10,751
for a long time
in a controlling environment.

258
00:17:11,721 --> 00:17:15,821
So today, we're going to practice
identifying your emotions.

259
00:17:18,231 --> 00:17:21,101
Now, to identify the emotion
you're feeling,

260
00:17:21,461 --> 00:17:25,471
- could you pick from these cards?
- Oh, okay.

261
00:17:33,381 --> 00:17:36,411
(Wronged)

262
00:17:42,681 --> 00:17:43,691
(Resentful)

263
00:17:45,521 --> 00:17:49,621
Wronged, resentful, guilty.

264
00:17:50,961 --> 00:17:54,761
Which of those emotions
is the strongest, Father?

265
00:17:55,261 --> 00:17:56,931
Feeling wronged.

266
00:17:58,101 --> 00:18:00,671
Why did I have to suffer like that?

267
00:18:01,341 --> 00:18:05,071
Why did Jo Mi Hyang
hit me in the head with a rock?

268
00:18:05,541 --> 00:18:07,481
And why did she trick me
into thinking...

269
00:18:07,541 --> 00:18:09,611
I was a murderer
when I'd lost my memory,

270
00:18:10,211 --> 00:18:13,521
and then lock me up
and exploit me for 30 years?

271
00:18:14,881 --> 00:18:16,951
She likely saw you
as a replacement...

272
00:18:16,991 --> 00:18:19,821
for her dead older brother
and became obsessed.

273
00:18:22,361 --> 00:18:26,361
Then what part
makes you feel guilty?

274
00:18:26,931 --> 00:18:31,601
That my real family had to live
without me because of what happened.

275
00:18:32,901 --> 00:18:37,111
And this horrible thing that
happened today is all my fault too.

276
00:18:37,271 --> 00:18:41,041
No. It's not your fault, Father.
It's Jo Mi Hyang's.

277
00:18:41,611 --> 00:18:44,651
You're the victim, Father.
And so are we.

278
00:18:46,111 --> 00:18:47,951
But there's good news too, Father.

279
00:18:48,721 --> 00:18:53,961
You're now free
from her psychological manipulation.

280
00:19:01,231 --> 00:19:02,561
They all turned you down?

281
00:19:02,801 --> 00:19:06,471
Yes. They're all hesitant,
saying new brands don't last.

282
00:19:06,941 --> 00:19:10,711
I mean, it's not like we'll be a new
brand forever. That's so unfair.

283
00:19:11,071 --> 00:19:13,711
We need to get
the main samples made quickly.

284
00:19:14,241 --> 00:19:18,681
Is there anyone here
who can make the samples?

285
00:19:20,481 --> 00:19:23,591
I could, but the quality
won't match a professional's.

286
00:19:24,191 --> 00:19:25,821
CEO Gong is the best one at it.

287
00:19:26,221 --> 00:19:27,821
I'm just okay at it.

288
00:19:28,161 --> 00:19:29,361
There's no other option.

289
00:19:29,421 --> 00:19:31,961
Since we're pressed for time,
you do it, CEO Gong.

290
00:19:32,061 --> 00:19:35,031
- I'm leaving.
- What? Director Yang!

291
00:19:35,861 --> 00:19:38,501
Hey! I thought you said
you'd overcome the crisis.

292
00:19:38,901 --> 00:19:42,241
Gosh, that guy. He's always
dumping everything on me.

293
00:19:46,141 --> 00:19:47,181
Oh, Woo Jae, what is it?

294
00:19:48,281 --> 00:19:49,951
What? Grandma?

295
00:19:55,051 --> 00:19:57,551
Hey, how's Father doing?

296
00:19:58,391 --> 00:19:59,921
He's still just sitting
in the living room.

297
00:20:00,891 --> 00:20:02,891
I think he feels too guilty
to even come in.

298
00:20:04,031 --> 00:20:08,031
I checked on his emotional state
with the cards today,

299
00:20:08,231 --> 00:20:10,001
and he's feeling
a great deal of guilt.

300
00:20:11,831 --> 00:20:15,341
If he keeps blaming himself,
it'll slow down his recovery.

301
00:20:15,771 --> 00:20:19,111
That's right.
If the self-blame gets worse,

302
00:20:19,441 --> 00:20:22,111
he could lose the will
to recover at all.

303
00:20:22,911 --> 00:20:24,551
I'll see if I can find something...

304
00:20:24,651 --> 00:20:26,851
to help him find some
emotional stability.

305
00:20:35,161 --> 00:20:37,231
(Guilt)

306
00:20:42,261 --> 00:20:44,871
Bring him back.
Bring him back, I said.

307
00:20:51,171 --> 00:20:52,311
Grandfather.

308
00:20:53,711 --> 00:20:56,411
Why are you out so late?
It's dangerous.

309
00:20:56,951 --> 00:20:58,751
That's why I escorted her home.

310
00:21:00,081 --> 00:21:01,951
You're all going through so much
because of me.

311
00:21:02,181 --> 00:21:06,191
Not at all, Grandfather.
But how is Grandma doing?

312
00:21:06,321 --> 00:21:10,291
She's sleeping inside on an IV.
Say hi later and go on up.

313
00:21:10,991 --> 00:21:11,991
Okay.

314
00:21:12,691 --> 00:21:13,701
What's that?

315
00:21:13,931 --> 00:21:17,671
Oh, it's fabric.
I have to work on a sample urgently.

316
00:21:18,031 --> 00:21:19,101
Oh, really?

317
00:21:20,201 --> 00:21:21,471
Why, Grandfather?

318
00:21:22,641 --> 00:21:23,841
Well, the thing is...

319
00:21:49,661 --> 00:21:50,701
Father.

320
00:21:51,401 --> 00:21:53,801
I'm off to play a round
with Councilor Hwang.

321
00:21:53,871 --> 00:21:55,171
Have a good game.

322
00:21:55,941 --> 00:21:56,941
Are you itchy?

323
00:21:57,541 --> 00:22:00,311
Want to go to the sauna?
Should I give you a good scrub-down?

324
00:22:00,481 --> 00:22:04,551
A good scrub and an oil massage
would make your skin so soft.

325
00:22:04,651 --> 00:22:06,151
No, thanks. You go.

326
00:22:06,751 --> 00:22:09,021
Father, we're here.

327
00:22:09,181 --> 00:22:11,651
Sounds like Dong Suk is here.
I'll get going now.

328
00:22:12,221 --> 00:22:13,221
Okay.

329
00:22:21,361 --> 00:22:23,771
I really love chicken.

330
00:22:24,501 --> 00:22:27,071
Really? Please, eat a lot.

331
00:22:27,671 --> 00:22:30,041
They say a son-in-law gets the best hen
when he visits his in-laws.

332
00:22:30,741 --> 00:22:31,771
That's right.

333
00:22:32,211 --> 00:22:36,881
Also, from now on, just think
of me as your mother-in-law.

334
00:22:37,081 --> 00:22:39,851
Oh, yes? Yes.

335
00:22:39,911 --> 00:22:42,421
- Mother-in-law.
- Gosh, Mom.

336
00:22:44,991 --> 00:22:47,561
Ji Hu, how do you like having
your own room? It's great.

337
00:22:47,661 --> 00:22:49,721
It's not just good. It's awesome.

338
00:22:50,861 --> 00:22:52,931
Do you know what a pigsty
his room is?

339
00:22:52,991 --> 00:22:55,031
Since his aunt and uncle
were coming today,

340
00:22:55,101 --> 00:22:58,631
- he spent all morning cleaning.
- I take after you.

341
00:22:59,531 --> 00:23:02,171
You should've brought Gi Cheol with you.
We could've played some janggi.

342
00:23:02,271 --> 00:23:04,371
It's still not easy
for him to go out.

343
00:23:04,611 --> 00:23:07,011
But, Father,
if his memory comes back,

344
00:23:07,011 --> 00:23:08,541
can he practice medicine again?

345
00:23:08,711 --> 00:23:10,551
Well, the gap in his career
is too long,

346
00:23:10,651 --> 00:23:13,111
so treating or diagnosing
patients would be difficult,

347
00:23:13,421 --> 00:23:16,281
but I think he could still handle
patient interviews or consultations.

348
00:23:17,221 --> 00:23:18,521
Father-in-law.

349
00:23:19,221 --> 00:23:21,991
The other day,
my brother was seeing a patient.

350
00:23:22,191 --> 00:23:26,591
Father was just watching
from the side when suddenly...

351
00:23:26,661 --> 00:23:28,201
he just blurted out the diagnosis.

352
00:23:28,961 --> 00:23:29,961
Really?

353
00:23:30,031 --> 00:23:34,101
Wow, I thought that was all a lie,
but things like that really happen.

354
00:23:34,341 --> 00:23:35,601
Don't just let him stay at home.

355
00:23:35,671 --> 00:23:37,571
He needs to do something
to get his energy back.

356
00:23:37,911 --> 00:23:38,911
Yes, sir.

357
00:23:38,971 --> 00:23:40,541
My sister-in-law
is looking for something...

358
00:23:40,611 --> 00:23:41,681
that might lift his spirits.

359
00:23:42,081 --> 00:23:43,381
It's such a relief, isn't it?

360
00:23:43,451 --> 00:23:45,381
Having a mental health
doctor in the family.

361
00:23:45,711 --> 00:23:46,711
Yes.

362
00:23:46,781 --> 00:23:49,651
Oh my, have you completely
warmed up to the Dr. Han?

363
00:23:50,021 --> 00:23:52,221
Of course.
We're family by marriage now.

364
00:23:53,661 --> 00:23:55,491
Hurry and eat, everyone.
It's getting cold.

365
00:23:55,561 --> 00:23:57,591
- Well then, let's eat.
- Yes.

366
00:23:57,661 --> 00:24:01,761
- Thanks for the food.
- Thank you for the meal.

367
00:24:08,441 --> 00:24:10,271
Where are we going
that's so far away?

368
00:24:10,841 --> 00:24:12,871
A dessert cafe
I went to with my girlfriend.

369
00:24:13,841 --> 00:24:15,441
You should definitely bring
your girlfriend next time.

370
00:24:15,881 --> 00:24:17,211
Dad will treat you guys
to something good.

371
00:24:17,481 --> 00:24:18,481
Okay.

372
00:24:21,121 --> 00:24:24,221
Oh, my. Well, hello there.

373
00:24:24,291 --> 00:24:26,651
Oh my, how old are you?
How many months?

374
00:24:26,721 --> 00:24:29,691
- She's 14 months now.
- Oh, 14 months?

375
00:24:29,991 --> 00:24:31,291
She must be teething a lot.

376
00:24:31,761 --> 00:24:36,431
- Is Mom having a hard time?
- Yes, it is a war every night.

377
00:24:36,631 --> 00:24:40,341
Oh my, what's her name?
Gosh, you're so pretty.

378
00:24:40,401 --> 00:24:41,801
Oh, you're just the cutest.

379
00:24:43,141 --> 00:24:47,511
Oh, so pretty. Oh my, let me.

380
00:24:48,981 --> 00:24:50,551
- Thank you.
- Oh my.

381
00:24:51,051 --> 00:24:54,421
Bye-bye. Bye now. Let's go.

382
00:24:55,481 --> 00:24:57,051
Hold on.

383
00:24:57,051 --> 00:25:01,161
Wait a minute, Eun Bin.
What are you filming with me?

384
00:25:02,361 --> 00:25:06,091
Before-and-after styling photos.

385
00:25:07,931 --> 00:25:10,001
You want me to be the model?

386
00:25:10,061 --> 00:25:13,941
Yes. Why? You said you'd help me.
Wait here a second.

387
00:25:19,341 --> 00:25:20,541
Okay, step out.

388
00:25:21,381 --> 00:25:23,181
You look great.

389
00:25:24,811 --> 00:25:28,181
Radiating a natural, masculine vibe.
Come on out.

390
00:25:28,751 --> 00:25:29,951
This isn't bad.

391
00:25:34,391 --> 00:25:36,661
Cute.

392
00:25:42,461 --> 00:25:45,431
This is good. It's exactly
the look I was imagining.

393
00:25:46,031 --> 00:25:47,401
First, I'll get an upper-body shot,

394
00:25:47,471 --> 00:25:49,241
then full-body shots
from the front and back.

395
00:25:49,501 --> 00:25:50,511
Right.

396
00:25:52,871 --> 00:25:54,981
And then full-body.

397
00:25:55,641 --> 00:25:56,911
Turn around for me.

398
00:25:58,711 --> 00:25:59,711
Okay, got it.

399
00:26:05,091 --> 00:26:06,121
What's wrong?

400
00:26:10,161 --> 00:26:11,461
What are you doing?

401
00:26:11,561 --> 00:26:14,131
What do you think I'm doing?
I'm styling you.

402
00:26:14,201 --> 00:26:15,401
Just hold still.

403
00:26:24,371 --> 00:26:25,441
Oh my.

404
00:26:26,311 --> 00:26:27,441
Hey, Ji Hu.

405
00:26:28,081 --> 00:26:29,311
What are you two doing?

406
00:26:31,781 --> 00:26:35,021
Your sister needed a portfolio,
and we're almost done.

407
00:26:35,081 --> 00:26:36,281
Just wait a moment.

408
00:26:36,351 --> 00:26:39,691
He's just helping me.
Don't get the wrong idea.

409
00:26:40,321 --> 00:26:42,821
If that's all it was,
couldn't I have helped?

410
00:26:45,891 --> 00:26:48,931
You're right. Gosh.
I guess I didn't think of that.

411
00:26:49,601 --> 00:26:50,671
Anyway.

412
00:26:51,001 --> 00:26:53,001
It's nice to see
the in-laws are so close.

413
00:26:55,371 --> 00:26:58,111
Hey, you. Go hit the books.

414
00:26:58,171 --> 00:27:00,981
What was your rank on the last exam?

415
00:27:05,251 --> 00:27:06,251
My gosh.

416
00:27:06,451 --> 00:27:07,521
(3H Acupressure Bed)

417
00:27:07,521 --> 00:27:09,221
- Oh, honey.
- Oh, my.

418
00:27:09,681 --> 00:27:10,791
Councilor Hwang.

419
00:27:11,391 --> 00:27:12,921
It's been a while, sir.

420
00:27:12,991 --> 00:27:16,961
It certainly has. I'm sorry to come
empty-handed on my first visit.

421
00:27:17,131 --> 00:27:20,631
Not at all.
It's an honor just to have you here.

422
00:27:21,461 --> 00:27:24,901
You should have given me a heads-up.

423
00:27:24,971 --> 00:27:27,841
Councilor Hwang
finished his round of golf,

424
00:27:27,901 --> 00:27:30,611
and said he was feeling stiff
all over.

425
00:27:32,471 --> 00:27:34,141
Of course.

426
00:27:34,381 --> 00:27:36,741
- Please, give it a try.
- Should I?

427
00:27:36,811 --> 00:27:37,811
Yes.

428
00:27:38,351 --> 00:27:39,751
- Right this way.
- Please, go ahead.

429
00:27:42,281 --> 00:27:44,021
How is it, Councilor Hwang?

430
00:27:45,191 --> 00:27:47,361
The way it presses firmly
on my back...

431
00:27:47,891 --> 00:27:49,791
I feel the fatigue melting away.

432
00:27:51,191 --> 00:27:53,831
It's very popular with golfers.

433
00:27:53,901 --> 00:27:55,901
This feels so refreshing.

434
00:27:58,201 --> 00:27:59,231
You should come more often.

435
00:28:03,571 --> 00:28:04,571
Feels good, doesn't it?

436
00:28:05,311 --> 00:28:07,381
- It feels wonderful.
- I'm glad.

437
00:28:07,541 --> 00:28:09,511
I had a wonderful time today,
Dr. Yang.

438
00:28:09,681 --> 00:28:11,711
Yes. Get home safely,
Councilor Hwang.

439
00:28:12,811 --> 00:28:14,621
- Get home safely.
- Thank you.

440
00:28:14,681 --> 00:28:15,681
Take care, sir.

441
00:28:16,981 --> 00:28:19,791
Oh my gosh, honey. Congratulations.

442
00:28:19,851 --> 00:28:22,721
It's not a sure thing yet.

443
00:28:22,891 --> 00:28:26,591
Come on. If Councilor Hwang is
backing you, it's as good as done.

444
00:28:26,961 --> 00:28:28,701
Right?

445
00:28:30,301 --> 00:28:31,701
Honey.

446
00:28:31,971 --> 00:28:34,801
Is my Se Ri about to become
a councilor's wife?

447
00:28:35,071 --> 00:28:38,971
- Oh my gosh.
- Wow, you already look dignified.

448
00:28:50,351 --> 00:28:54,821
- How are you feeling?
- I feel much better after the IV.

449
00:28:55,121 --> 00:28:56,861
But why were you just sitting there?

450
00:28:57,061 --> 00:28:59,891
I heard a sewing machine upstairs.

451
00:29:00,331 --> 00:29:03,131
I guess Ju Ah
must be making something.

452
00:29:04,101 --> 00:29:05,231
Want to go see?

453
00:29:07,971 --> 00:29:09,571
(Work Order)

454
00:29:13,981 --> 00:29:14,981
Ju Ah.

455
00:29:15,541 --> 00:29:19,051
Grandma, are you okay?
You didn't get hurt anywhere else?

456
00:29:19,111 --> 00:29:21,121
Yes, I'm feeling a little better.

457
00:29:22,621 --> 00:29:24,891
But what brings you
and Grandfather here?

458
00:29:24,991 --> 00:29:27,661
Your grandfather was curious.

459
00:29:28,091 --> 00:29:29,091
About what?

460
00:29:29,091 --> 00:29:31,561
The sound was nostalgic.

461
00:29:32,691 --> 00:29:34,001
Is it okay if I watch?

462
00:29:34,261 --> 00:29:35,431
Yes.

463
00:29:36,201 --> 00:29:37,631
Don't mind me. Just keep working.

464
00:29:37,971 --> 00:29:40,641
- Okay, I'm a bit busy, so...
- Right.

465
00:29:41,501 --> 00:29:42,501
Okay.

466
00:29:45,141 --> 00:29:46,141
Mother?

467
00:29:48,641 --> 00:29:49,681
What?

468
00:29:50,411 --> 00:29:51,411
Where did she go?

469
00:29:56,481 --> 00:29:59,821
- What are you all doing here?
- Oh, we're watching Ju Ah work.

470
00:30:00,151 --> 00:30:01,521
Father seems to be enjoying it.

471
00:30:05,361 --> 00:30:08,231
I guess the familiar fabrics
bring him a sense of comfort.

472
00:30:09,001 --> 00:30:10,101
I guess so.

473
00:30:12,331 --> 00:30:14,441
Why does the fabric
keep bunching up?

474
00:30:16,101 --> 00:30:18,541
With a stretchy fabric like this,

475
00:30:18,811 --> 00:30:21,311
it'll bunch up
if the presser foot pressure is too high.

476
00:30:22,181 --> 00:30:26,311
- What?
- Lower the presser foot pressure,

477
00:30:26,751 --> 00:30:29,551
and loosen the upper thread tension,

478
00:30:30,221 --> 00:30:32,351
and try adjusting the stitch length.

479
00:30:33,391 --> 00:30:34,391
Oh, that's right.

480
00:30:34,391 --> 00:30:36,761
You did alterations for a long time,
didn't you, Grandfather?

481
00:30:37,631 --> 00:30:38,961
I did alterations,

482
00:30:39,031 --> 00:30:42,201
and I occasionally made
custom clothes too.

483
00:30:43,001 --> 00:30:44,731
Then, by any chance,

484
00:30:45,071 --> 00:30:48,641
- could you make one based on this?
- What?

485
00:30:53,981 --> 00:30:55,381
I think I can.

486
00:30:56,111 --> 00:30:57,111
Really?

487
00:31:17,971 --> 00:31:19,071
I'm home.

488
00:31:25,171 --> 00:31:27,311
- What's everyone doing in here?
- Oh, honey.

489
00:31:27,381 --> 00:31:28,381
There.

490
00:31:28,681 --> 00:31:32,381
- Did you make this, Father?
- Yes.

491
00:31:33,981 --> 00:31:34,981
What do you think, Ju Ah?

492
00:31:35,081 --> 00:31:38,621
Wow, this is insane.
Grandfather, you're so fast,

493
00:31:38,691 --> 00:31:40,421
and the sewing quality is amazing.

494
00:31:40,991 --> 00:31:42,561
Thank goodness.

495
00:31:43,061 --> 00:31:44,961
I'm just glad it turned out well.

496
00:31:45,691 --> 00:31:49,761
I mean, Father's suturing skills
have always been top-notch.

497
00:31:49,831 --> 00:31:52,271
Oh, that's right. Ju Ah's talent,

498
00:31:52,431 --> 00:31:55,201
she must have gotten her skills
from her grandfather, right?

499
00:31:55,271 --> 00:31:56,841
I guess so.

500
00:31:57,471 --> 00:31:59,771
Grandfather, thank you so much.

501
00:32:01,311 --> 00:32:02,541
Should I do the others for you?

502
00:32:03,181 --> 00:32:05,851
Really? I would be so grateful
if you did.

503
00:32:06,211 --> 00:32:07,281
- Oh my.
- Then let's do it.

504
00:32:07,621 --> 00:32:10,021
Looks like our Ju Ah
really hit the jackpot, right?

505
00:32:10,851 --> 00:32:12,391
This one is a skirt.

506
00:32:12,791 --> 00:32:17,091
- A skirt. It's a set.
- Wow, a matching top and bottom?

507
00:32:17,161 --> 00:32:18,931
- Yes.
- Okay.

508
00:32:20,761 --> 00:32:23,601
He looks really happy, doesn't he?

509
00:32:23,831 --> 00:32:26,701
Right? Ju Ah did something great
without even realizing it.

510
00:32:27,201 --> 00:32:29,801
I just thought that
seeing the sewing machine...

511
00:32:29,871 --> 00:32:33,441
might bring back bad memories,
and I was worried he'd be upset.

512
00:32:33,711 --> 00:32:35,641
By proving his skills to himself,

513
00:32:35,711 --> 00:32:37,881
his sense of self-worth
is increasing.

514
00:32:38,051 --> 00:32:39,551
You think so?

515
00:32:42,281 --> 00:32:43,881
You found a sample maker?

516
00:32:44,221 --> 00:32:46,151
- Who?
- My grandfather.

517
00:32:49,661 --> 00:32:53,391
He did alterations for 30 years
and apparently made custom clothing too.

518
00:32:54,161 --> 00:32:55,461
Even so,

519
00:32:55,701 --> 00:32:58,571
don't you think it's a bit much
to ask of your grandfather?

520
00:32:59,271 --> 00:33:01,371
Are you looking down
on my grandfather?

521
00:33:01,771 --> 00:33:03,571
No, that's not it.
I'm not looking down on him.

522
00:33:04,741 --> 00:33:07,781
Making samples for a brand
is no easy task.

523
00:33:08,211 --> 00:33:10,081
I'm just worried that
if they aren't made exactly to spec,

524
00:33:10,141 --> 00:33:14,051
- it will throw off our schedule.
- Oh, you don't think I know that?

525
00:33:14,051 --> 00:33:15,381
The sample quality is practically
at an artisan...

526
00:33:15,451 --> 00:33:18,191
Then let's decide
after we see a sample.

527
00:33:18,621 --> 00:33:21,921
No, the decision is mine to make.
I'll be the judge.

528
00:33:24,161 --> 00:33:25,161
All right.

529
00:33:26,991 --> 00:33:29,401
Gosh, he really knows how to
rain on my parade, doesn't he?

530
00:33:29,461 --> 00:33:31,831
I try to make things easier for him,
and this is the thanks I get.

531
00:33:37,271 --> 00:33:40,311
You think that woman is still
in our neighborhood?

532
00:33:41,811 --> 00:33:42,811
Who knows.

533
00:33:43,841 --> 00:33:45,251
Anyway, let's be careful, Dolphin.

534
00:33:45,711 --> 00:33:46,711
Okay.

535
00:33:47,881 --> 00:33:49,481
By the way, Tamin,

536
00:33:50,221 --> 00:33:52,321
you really seemed to love
that baby earlier.

537
00:33:53,291 --> 00:33:54,561
That baby was just adorable, right?

538
00:33:56,061 --> 00:33:58,861
- Hey, maybe we...
- I love you.

539
00:33:59,391 --> 00:34:00,391
What?

540
00:34:02,261 --> 00:34:03,331
I'm happy with how things are
right now.

541
00:34:06,771 --> 00:34:07,771
This feels nice and cool.

542
00:34:10,171 --> 00:34:11,171
Here.

543
00:34:11,471 --> 00:34:15,441
Wow, Grandfather,
you're unbelievably fast.

544
00:34:15,611 --> 00:34:17,751
I hope it turned out all right.

545
00:34:18,181 --> 00:34:19,551
The details are so clean,

546
00:34:19,611 --> 00:34:22,281
and the silhouette is exactly
what I had in mind.

547
00:34:23,681 --> 00:34:24,691
Gi Cheol,

548
00:34:25,051 --> 00:34:27,721
let's stop for today and continue
tomorrow. You must be exhausted.

549
00:34:27,791 --> 00:34:29,191
- All right, shall we?
- Yes.

550
00:34:29,261 --> 00:34:30,731
I lost track of time.

551
00:34:30,791 --> 00:34:33,931
I'm so sorry, Grandfather.

552
00:34:34,101 --> 00:34:36,231
No, I had a wonderful time.

553
00:34:37,031 --> 00:34:38,571
Thank you so much.

554
00:34:38,931 --> 00:34:41,771
- Ju Ah, you get some rest too.
- Okay. You too.

555
00:34:41,841 --> 00:34:42,841
- Okay.
- Right.

556
00:34:43,441 --> 00:34:45,011
Incredible.

557
00:34:47,541 --> 00:34:51,781
- Gosh, Father. Aren't you tired?
- I'm fine.

558
00:34:52,411 --> 00:34:54,651
Father, you look like
you're in a great mood.

559
00:34:54,721 --> 00:34:56,651
I am. I'm full of energy.

560
00:34:57,491 --> 00:34:59,651
- Everyone, go in and get some rest.
- Okay.

561
00:34:59,691 --> 00:35:00,921
You get some rest too.

562
00:35:01,961 --> 00:35:02,991
Well...

563
00:35:04,761 --> 00:35:06,261
Can I sleep in our room tonight?

564
00:35:08,361 --> 00:35:10,001
Father.

565
00:35:10,801 --> 00:35:12,831
You want to sleep with Mom?

566
00:35:13,501 --> 00:35:17,241
Yes.
I want to take care of your mother.

567
00:35:29,821 --> 00:35:30,821
Do I make you uncomfortable?

568
00:35:31,951 --> 00:35:32,951
No.

569
00:35:34,191 --> 00:35:36,261
You're my husband.
Why would I be uncomfortable?

570
00:35:37,391 --> 00:35:38,931
Then rest well.

571
00:35:42,901 --> 00:35:44,171
About the tailoring...

572
00:35:44,931 --> 00:35:46,571
How did you get into it?

573
00:35:52,541 --> 00:35:54,981
It was like I'd just woken up,

574
00:35:55,711 --> 00:35:58,281
and suddenly, my name, my age...

575
00:35:58,811 --> 00:36:00,751
I couldn't remember anything.

576
00:36:01,381 --> 00:36:03,751
There wasn't a single thing
I knew how to do.

577
00:36:04,821 --> 00:36:07,051
But then,

578
00:36:07,661 --> 00:36:09,661
Mi Hyang from the Tailor Shop,

579
00:36:10,091 --> 00:36:12,731
brought some work home,
saying she was learning the trade.

580
00:36:13,361 --> 00:36:16,001
Cutting, sewing,
putting it all together...

581
00:36:16,061 --> 00:36:18,301
Turns out, I was really good at it.

582
00:36:19,371 --> 00:36:21,371
And you never thought,

583
00:36:21,971 --> 00:36:25,071
- that you might be a doctor?
- I couldn't.

584
00:36:25,811 --> 00:36:27,941
I couldn't remember anything.

585
00:36:31,011 --> 00:36:33,181
I really am good at it.

586
00:36:34,521 --> 00:36:37,081
I'll make you an outfit next time.

587
00:36:38,391 --> 00:36:39,391
But I...

588
00:36:40,921 --> 00:36:42,561
already received clothes...

589
00:36:43,521 --> 00:36:44,591
that you made.

590
00:36:46,231 --> 00:36:47,531
Jo Mi Hyang.

591
00:36:48,001 --> 00:36:50,231
A cardigan and a padded vest,

592
00:36:50,901 --> 00:36:53,771
she brought them to me,
saying you had made them.

593
00:36:54,471 --> 00:36:55,741
That woman isn't just
a little crazy.

594
00:36:55,741 --> 00:36:57,541
She's completely out of her mind.

595
00:37:49,291 --> 00:37:52,291
Today marks one year since you left.

596
00:37:53,291 --> 00:37:55,631
Every time Ju Ah hears
the front gate open,

597
00:37:56,101 --> 00:37:58,171
she runs out, calling for
her Grandfather.

598
00:37:59,331 --> 00:38:01,941
Hearing "Grandfather" come
from her little mouth...

599
00:38:02,571 --> 00:38:05,011
is just so heartbreaking.

600
00:38:09,681 --> 00:38:12,681
People tell me to forget about you,

601
00:38:13,051 --> 00:38:14,821
and move on.

602
00:38:15,981 --> 00:38:17,221
But honey,

603
00:38:17,921 --> 00:38:19,051
Jeong Han's father,

604
00:38:20,451 --> 00:38:22,561
I can't forget you.

605
00:38:24,121 --> 00:38:28,561
Everything I see reminds me of you.

606
00:38:30,261 --> 00:38:32,731
Is it hatred or resentment,

607
00:38:33,531 --> 00:38:34,841
or longing?

608
00:38:36,441 --> 00:38:39,271
My heart is still full of you.

609
00:38:40,771 --> 00:38:42,741
How many of these letters
must I write,

610
00:38:43,441 --> 00:38:45,011
for you to come back?

611
00:39:09,671 --> 00:39:10,671
Seong Mi,

612
00:39:11,041 --> 00:39:13,271
your radiation therapy
starts tomorrow, right?

613
00:39:13,671 --> 00:39:15,881
Yes. They said
I don't need a guardian,

614
00:39:15,941 --> 00:39:19,251
- so I'll go by myself.
- By yourself? I'm going with you.

615
00:39:19,651 --> 00:39:23,421
- You're busy. I'll go.
- It's fine. It stresses me out...

616
00:39:23,481 --> 00:39:25,751
more that everyone has to
take time off for me.

617
00:39:25,991 --> 00:39:29,291
No, you can't. It's too dangerous
for you to go alone right now.

618
00:39:29,791 --> 00:39:30,791
He's right.

619
00:39:31,261 --> 00:39:33,961
We don't know
who that woman will target next.

620
00:39:34,131 --> 00:39:36,301
Don't say that. It's scary.

621
00:39:36,761 --> 00:39:38,271
Everyone, I...

622
00:39:38,531 --> 00:39:41,371
Father, don't you dare feel guilty.

623
00:39:43,441 --> 00:39:44,511
Okay.

624
00:39:45,171 --> 00:39:47,781
But I want to get some exercise
in the morning.

625
00:39:47,841 --> 00:39:49,511
- Father.
- Yes?

626
00:39:49,541 --> 00:39:53,251
- It's dangerous for now.
- That's right. Just stay home.

627
00:39:53,881 --> 00:39:57,121
Don't worry.
I'm not afraid of that woman at all.

628
00:39:58,791 --> 00:40:00,191
Don't you all worry.

629
00:40:00,821 --> 00:40:02,361
I'm Gong Gi Cheol.

630
00:40:02,691 --> 00:40:04,631
I'm the head of this household.
Got it?

631
00:40:09,561 --> 00:40:12,831
Oh, right. Father.
Don't you remember this place?

632
00:40:13,601 --> 00:40:16,741
We all used to come here
every weekend to exercise.

633
00:40:17,471 --> 00:40:19,541
No wonder it feels familiar.

634
00:40:20,071 --> 00:40:21,681
Yes, we'd sometimes bring gimbap,

635
00:40:21,741 --> 00:40:23,881
and Jeong Han and you
would play the guitar,

636
00:40:23,941 --> 00:40:25,751
and we'd all sing together.

637
00:40:25,811 --> 00:40:28,451
- That's right.
- We should do that again sometime.

638
00:40:28,781 --> 00:40:29,781
Sounds great.

639
00:40:30,481 --> 00:40:34,661
Oh, but I saw you here last winter.

640
00:40:34,961 --> 00:40:35,961
You did?

641
00:40:36,991 --> 00:40:39,061
I've never been here in the winter.

642
00:40:39,531 --> 00:40:44,261
That's right.
Father, Mom mistook someone for you.

643
00:40:44,361 --> 00:40:46,171
She hit some guy on the head
and choked him,

644
00:40:46,231 --> 00:40:47,571
so she got taken to the
Police Substation.

645
00:40:47,631 --> 00:40:50,201
- Hey, Gong Dae Han.
- Right. That's right.

646
00:40:51,071 --> 00:40:54,841
- You did?
- Hey, he looked exactly like you.

647
00:40:56,111 --> 00:40:59,411
Wow, you must have missed me so much
you started seeing things.

648
00:41:01,081 --> 00:41:03,151
Father, are you making
a joke right now?

649
00:41:05,651 --> 00:41:08,621
Hey, did Father just make a joke?

650
00:41:10,091 --> 00:41:11,391
It's because you missed her, right?

651
00:41:11,661 --> 00:41:12,661
I guess so.

652
00:41:14,831 --> 00:41:17,231
Wait, Jeong Han.
Father, want to try this?

653
00:41:17,361 --> 00:41:19,431
Mom is really good at this.

654
00:41:20,171 --> 00:41:22,071
Father, will you be okay?

655
00:41:22,401 --> 00:41:23,671
Yes, I'll give it a try.

656
00:41:24,001 --> 00:41:25,771
- Be careful. Careful.
- Careful.

657
00:41:27,941 --> 00:41:30,241
- Father, careful.
- Careful.

658
00:41:32,411 --> 00:41:33,511
Wow.

659
00:41:36,521 --> 00:41:38,491
Your grandfather made all of this?

660
00:41:38,551 --> 00:41:41,921
Yes. Objectively,
what do you all think?

661
00:41:42,061 --> 00:41:45,631
Wow, the sewing quality
is excellent.

662
00:41:45,961 --> 00:41:48,601
The finishing is so clean
we won't have to make any revisions.

663
00:41:49,861 --> 00:41:54,401
- Did you hear that?
- Yes. It's not as bad as I feared.

664
00:41:55,301 --> 00:41:57,441
You have such a nice way
of putting things, don't you?

665
00:42:00,071 --> 00:42:01,311
Now that we have the main sample,

666
00:42:01,381 --> 00:42:03,241
we should meet with
the platform's marketing team.

667
00:42:03,311 --> 00:42:04,651
You can go ahead
and schedule the meeting, right?

668
00:42:04,981 --> 00:42:05,981
That's the plan.

669
00:42:06,251 --> 00:42:09,451
At the meeting, they'll ask about
specifics like the production plan,

670
00:42:09,521 --> 00:42:10,951
so what's the plan
for our production volume?

671
00:42:11,251 --> 00:42:13,951
Oh, well, the budget
needs to be finalized first...

672
00:42:14,021 --> 00:42:16,691
You still haven't finalized it?
What have you been doing?

673
00:42:17,291 --> 00:42:19,091
Just because we're past
the sample crisis,

674
00:42:19,161 --> 00:42:20,931
you're already pressuring me
about money?

675
00:42:21,061 --> 00:42:23,431
Of course I am.
Depending on the budget,

676
00:42:23,501 --> 00:42:25,401
the fabric grade and
material quality will change,

677
00:42:25,471 --> 00:42:28,001
and if the unit price doesn't work,
we'll have to revise the design.

678
00:42:29,801 --> 00:42:32,341
All right. I'll talk
to the Vice President...

679
00:42:32,471 --> 00:42:34,471
Hurry up! Okay?

680
00:42:34,541 --> 00:42:36,981
Go, go. Hurry up!

681
00:42:37,181 --> 00:42:38,351
- My gosh.
- Gosh, so slow.

682
00:42:38,781 --> 00:42:40,481
- Go, go.
- What is wrong with her?

683
00:42:40,551 --> 00:42:42,921
Let's go. Hurry up.
Why are you so slow?

684
00:42:42,981 --> 00:42:44,181
It's taking an eternity. Hurry.

685
00:42:44,251 --> 00:42:45,851
At this rate,
when will we ever get there?

686
00:42:45,921 --> 00:42:46,921
Oh, for goodness' sake.

687
00:42:50,121 --> 00:42:52,661
Wait. You went to meet
Officer Jeong's parents?

688
00:42:53,461 --> 00:42:56,461
- Yes.
- When did things get serious?

689
00:42:56,901 --> 00:43:00,071
Surprised, aren't you?
It's all thanks to you.

690
00:43:00,601 --> 00:43:02,571
Me? I didn't do anything.

691
00:43:02,741 --> 00:43:06,111
Come on. You showed us what
a happy couple looks like every day.

692
00:43:06,241 --> 00:43:10,141
Oh, really? So I was subconsciously
promoting marriage?

693
00:43:10,641 --> 00:43:11,651
Exactly.

694
00:43:13,681 --> 00:43:16,621
By the way,
Mr. Gong is looking well today.

695
00:43:17,321 --> 00:43:20,251
Yes, his memory is
slowly coming back,

696
00:43:20,251 --> 00:43:21,321
and he seems to have more energy.

697
00:43:21,321 --> 00:43:22,821
He even went for a walk
this morning.

698
00:43:23,761 --> 00:43:24,891
That's such a relief.

699
00:43:25,631 --> 00:43:28,231
- Excuse me.
- Oh my.

700
00:43:30,161 --> 00:43:32,001
- Welcome.
- Hello, Mr. Gong.

701
00:43:33,331 --> 00:43:37,071
What the heck? Seriously.
I know you miss me,

702
00:43:37,171 --> 00:43:39,171
but you can't just leave your post
during work hours.

703
00:43:39,241 --> 00:43:41,441
I'm not off my post.

704
00:43:41,911 --> 00:43:44,341
I'm here to see Mr. Gong
about the investigation schedule.

705
00:43:44,611 --> 00:43:46,051
What is this about?

706
00:43:46,381 --> 00:43:48,181
Detective Jang wanted to know
if you're available...

707
00:43:48,251 --> 00:43:49,621
for further questioning
this evening.

708
00:43:49,681 --> 00:43:51,921
- He asked me to check with you.
- Yes, I'm available.

709
00:43:52,051 --> 00:43:54,621
Shall we come to your house
today then?

710
00:43:54,961 --> 00:43:56,421
No, I'll go to
the Police Substation.

711
00:43:56,521 --> 00:43:58,831
What? Father,
are you sure you'll be okay?

712
00:43:58,991 --> 00:44:02,361
- You should just do it at home...
- No, I'm fine. Really.

713
00:44:02,701 --> 00:44:05,501
- Okay, we'll see you then.
- Okay.

714
00:44:05,601 --> 00:44:06,601
Okay.

715
00:44:07,931 --> 00:44:10,141
- Mr. Gong, one moment.
- Why?

716
00:44:11,371 --> 00:44:12,371
Why? What is it?

717
00:44:15,281 --> 00:44:19,411
And? Your mother likes Jin Ah?

718
00:44:19,851 --> 00:44:23,151
Yes. She said she's personable,
friendly, bright, and wholesome.

719
00:44:23,381 --> 00:44:25,291
- She really likes her.
- She does?

720
00:44:26,491 --> 00:44:28,721
And? Did she tell you
to get married soon?

721
00:44:28,991 --> 00:44:30,661
- Yes.
- Really?

722
00:44:30,691 --> 00:44:35,001
Well, speaking of which,
Mr. Gong, how did you propose?

723
00:44:35,461 --> 00:44:36,461
Propose?

724
00:44:38,671 --> 00:44:40,871
- Are you going to propose?
- Quiet.

725
00:44:41,131 --> 00:44:43,641
You have to promise me
you'll keep it a secret from Jin Ah.

726
00:44:43,741 --> 00:44:44,911
Okay, quiet.

727
00:44:52,581 --> 00:44:53,581
(Cheongsimwon)

728
00:44:53,581 --> 00:44:55,321
This is a calming pill.

729
00:44:56,621 --> 00:44:58,091
Will this help?

730
00:44:59,191 --> 00:45:02,561
You said Ms. Na's been
startled awake in her sleep, right?

731
00:45:03,121 --> 00:45:05,261
Make sure she takes one
whenever she's startled.

732
00:45:05,531 --> 00:45:07,561
If she's still not sleeping well,
come back.

733
00:45:07,631 --> 00:45:08,931
I'll give you something else.

734
00:45:11,131 --> 00:45:12,871
Go wash up.

735
00:45:13,571 --> 00:45:15,571
The older you get,
the more you need to stay clean.

736
00:45:15,841 --> 00:45:18,171
Why are you scratching yourself
like that? It's filthy.

737
00:45:19,141 --> 00:45:20,141
Get out.

738
00:45:21,811 --> 00:45:23,581
By the way, don't you have a wife?

739
00:45:25,351 --> 00:45:26,481
Did she pass away?

740
00:45:27,511 --> 00:45:28,521
Yes.

741
00:45:29,281 --> 00:45:30,281
That's what happened.

742
00:45:31,791 --> 00:45:32,791
I'll get going.

743
00:45:35,021 --> 00:45:37,091
You should get your blood tested.

744
00:45:37,721 --> 00:45:39,331
Those splotches...

745
00:45:40,131 --> 00:45:41,901
They look like petechiae.

746
00:45:42,561 --> 00:45:44,731
Did your memory come back?

747
00:45:45,831 --> 00:45:47,131
What did I just say?

748
00:45:48,141 --> 00:45:50,501
Things just pop out of my mouth
without me realizing it.

749
00:45:50,771 --> 00:45:52,711
Still a long way to go.

750
00:45:53,271 --> 00:45:54,271
Get out, you punk.

751
00:45:56,341 --> 00:45:58,151
Gosh, thanks for this.

752
00:46:04,991 --> 00:46:06,951
All right.
Next, we just need to decide...

753
00:46:07,021 --> 00:46:08,961
when to start
the Night Market Project.

754
00:46:09,121 --> 00:46:13,491
Hey, how about fall?
The weather's cool then.

755
00:46:13,861 --> 00:46:14,961
Wouldn't summer be better?

756
00:46:15,431 --> 00:46:18,471
- During hot, tropical nights.
- Yes. That's a great idea.

757
00:46:18,731 --> 00:46:21,641
And let's link it
with the local currency.

758
00:46:22,601 --> 00:46:24,201
So, what's next...

759
00:46:24,601 --> 00:46:25,611
Jeong Han.

760
00:46:26,541 --> 00:46:27,871
I think...

761
00:46:28,941 --> 00:46:30,141
I'm going to get the nomination.

762
00:46:30,811 --> 00:46:33,951
Dong Ik, congratulations.

763
00:46:34,311 --> 00:46:37,821
Hey, did you get a heads-up
from Councilor Hwang or something?

764
00:46:38,391 --> 00:46:41,351
I received a very positive signal.

765
00:46:42,921 --> 00:46:44,521
For Councilor Hwang's
signature campaign pledge,

766
00:46:45,161 --> 00:46:47,691
he said I'm exactly the talent
he needs.

767
00:46:48,031 --> 00:46:51,931
- Hey, what's the pledge?
- I don't know yet.

768
00:46:52,871 --> 00:46:54,971
I'm curious.

769
00:46:55,641 --> 00:46:58,101
A landmark for our Onjeong.

770
00:46:59,171 --> 00:47:01,341
My heart races
just thinking about it.

771
00:47:04,341 --> 00:47:07,651
The funds are secured,
and the plans are all in place.

772
00:47:08,281 --> 00:47:11,421
Councilor, you just need
to win the people's hearts.

773
00:47:11,591 --> 00:47:14,221
Leave it to me.
I've been elected for...

774
00:47:14,291 --> 00:47:16,061
three consecutive terms in Onjeong.

775
00:47:16,421 --> 00:47:18,731
Even the people who dislike me,
if Taehan builds...

776
00:47:18,791 --> 00:47:20,291
its new headquarters in Onjeong,

777
00:47:20,991 --> 00:47:22,601
they'll welcome it with open arms.

778
00:47:25,271 --> 00:47:28,171
The opposition from the Onjeong Market
merchants will be fierce.

779
00:47:28,641 --> 00:47:31,101
Since the market is central
to our plan,

780
00:47:31,171 --> 00:47:34,541
we'll inevitably have to
clear it all out.

781
00:47:34,811 --> 00:47:36,241
Don't worry.

782
00:47:36,981 --> 00:47:38,951
I've already found
the right person for the job.

783
00:47:39,281 --> 00:47:41,381
Is that so?

784
00:47:42,521 --> 00:47:43,521
Well, that's a relief.

785
00:47:51,791 --> 00:47:53,061
(TH)

786
00:47:53,131 --> 00:47:54,661
(Group)

787
00:47:55,201 --> 00:47:57,061
Have a seat.

788
00:47:59,331 --> 00:48:01,871
Where are you considering
for the landmark?

789
00:48:02,471 --> 00:48:04,701
Where the money is.

790
00:48:05,171 --> 00:48:08,141
Sounds like you've
already picked a spot.

791
00:48:08,411 --> 00:48:09,911
It'll be a hassle if word gets out.

792
00:48:09,981 --> 00:48:11,711
Once it's confirmed,
I'll tell you first.

793
00:48:12,081 --> 00:48:15,021
What's the point of me knowing?
I'm clueless as it is.

794
00:48:15,881 --> 00:48:16,881
What about Hye Su?

795
00:48:18,421 --> 00:48:20,451
I've been tailing her a bit,

796
00:48:20,791 --> 00:48:22,521
and all she seems to do is
get wasted and pass out.

797
00:48:23,121 --> 00:48:25,331
And when she sobers up,
her only joy is to find me and beat me up.

798
00:48:25,931 --> 00:48:27,961
Pathetic.

799
00:48:30,601 --> 00:48:33,671
I know, right? I thought she'd
at least be sharpening her knives.

800
00:48:40,841 --> 00:48:42,281
That ridiculous bastard.

801
00:48:43,311 --> 00:48:45,711
Got it. Thank you, Manager Kim.

802
00:48:50,581 --> 00:48:51,591
What is it?

803
00:48:52,151 --> 00:48:55,091
It looks like that bastard Jun Hyeok
is tailing me.

804
00:48:56,221 --> 00:48:58,831
What's there to tail?
You're either at a bar or here.

805
00:48:59,831 --> 00:49:01,701
He's already reported
that the ex-employees...

806
00:49:01,761 --> 00:49:02,931
are working together again.

807
00:49:05,601 --> 00:49:08,001
He must think I'm sharpening
my knife for revenge.

808
00:49:08,231 --> 00:49:11,711
Exactly. We're just trying
to make a living here.

809
00:49:11,911 --> 00:49:13,871
Park Jun Hyeok isn't even human.

810
00:49:15,511 --> 00:49:17,511
Oh my, I'm sorry.

811
00:49:18,451 --> 00:49:21,181
But you're right.
He'll get what's coming to him.

812
00:49:21,981 --> 00:49:23,481
I hope he gets struck by lightning
and drops dead.

813
00:49:33,691 --> 00:49:35,761
(Magicful Receipt)

814
00:49:39,501 --> 00:49:41,641
What's all this? I thought
you were just getting donuts.

815
00:49:41,641 --> 00:49:43,301
Did you go grocery shopping?

816
00:49:43,441 --> 00:49:46,841
Well, there was so much good food,
so I bought a little of everything.

817
00:49:47,271 --> 00:49:49,081
- The receipt.
- Here you go.

818
00:49:51,181 --> 00:49:54,081
- It seems to suit you well.
- Yes, it's fun.

819
00:49:54,981 --> 00:49:56,221
Where's the calculator?

820
00:49:57,651 --> 00:49:59,151
Please.

821
00:50:04,421 --> 00:50:07,131
I guess I didn't get it after all.

822
00:50:11,671 --> 00:50:14,401
Yang Eun Bin.
Congratulations, you have passed...

823
00:50:14,471 --> 00:50:16,801
document screening stage.

824
00:50:17,341 --> 00:50:18,711
No way. Oh my gosh,
did I really get it?

825
00:50:19,311 --> 00:50:20,671
I can't believe it.

826
00:50:26,211 --> 00:50:30,081
- Hey. in-law!
- What?

827
00:50:30,151 --> 00:50:32,721
I passed the first round.
They want me to come in...

828
00:50:32,791 --> 00:50:34,151
for an interview tomorrow.

829
00:50:34,551 --> 00:50:38,961
- Really?
- Yes. I'm so excited.

830
00:50:39,261 --> 00:50:40,531
Eun Bin.

831
00:50:40,591 --> 00:50:42,731
This is all thanks to you.
I'll treat you...

832
00:50:42,801 --> 00:50:44,601
to something big, I promise, okay?

833
00:50:47,401 --> 00:50:48,541
Bye.

834
00:50:50,671 --> 00:50:52,871
I passed.

835
00:50:55,411 --> 00:50:56,581
My heart...

836
00:51:01,581 --> 00:51:05,421
Oh, my. Well, hello there.
Gosh, you're so pretty.

837
00:51:07,091 --> 00:51:09,091
(Discount on your first order
of any meat dish)

838
00:51:10,021 --> 00:51:13,531
- Gong Woo Jae.
- Yes, Aunt? What's wrong?

839
00:51:13,791 --> 00:51:15,861
- Why are you so startled?
- What?

840
00:51:17,931 --> 00:51:19,801
I just thought
you might've seen something.

841
00:51:20,271 --> 00:51:21,371
What would I have seen?

842
00:51:22,001 --> 00:51:23,541
It's nothing. Why?

843
00:51:24,601 --> 00:51:27,371
Uncle. He likes babies, doesn't he?

844
00:51:28,071 --> 00:51:31,011
Why? What are you getting at?

845
00:51:32,081 --> 00:51:34,151
I was just asking.

846
00:51:35,281 --> 00:51:36,421
Did you get the rubber gloves?

847
00:51:37,151 --> 00:51:39,291
I'll go get them right away.

848
00:51:39,351 --> 00:51:41,051
(Discount on your first order
of any meat dish)

849
00:51:47,531 --> 00:51:49,061
That's suspicious.

850
00:51:52,801 --> 00:51:55,301
Father, I'm home...

851
00:52:00,071 --> 00:52:04,241
(Medical Clinic)

852
00:52:04,811 --> 00:52:06,581
Your white blood cell count
is quite high.

853
00:52:06,651 --> 00:52:08,521
And you're already showing
signs of purpura.

854
00:52:08,681 --> 00:52:11,081
You need to go to a major hospital
with your family...

855
00:52:11,151 --> 00:52:13,091
without delay and get
a bone marrow test.

856
00:52:16,021 --> 00:52:17,561
(Deep-Tissue Acupressure and Massage
for Spinal Muscles)

857
00:52:17,621 --> 00:52:20,031
Your sales have improved
since last time.

858
00:52:20,761 --> 00:52:23,331
We can set a higher sales target.

859
00:52:23,931 --> 00:52:25,701
- Should we?
- Yes.

860
00:52:26,401 --> 00:52:30,501
Okay, then today let's talk about
how to handle customer returns.

861
00:52:31,001 --> 00:52:33,541
You're right. Those can be
really difficult to deal with.

862
00:52:33,741 --> 00:52:37,341
If you just give them a flat "no,"
it's hard to make any progress.

863
00:52:38,041 --> 00:52:40,011
Exactly what the problem is,

864
00:52:40,011 --> 00:52:42,021
and the specific reason
for their complaint,

865
00:52:42,081 --> 00:52:44,221
it's best to figure that out first.

866
00:52:44,421 --> 00:52:47,721
I see. Confirm their complaint.

867
00:52:50,361 --> 00:52:51,661
Just a moment, I'm sorry.

868
00:52:54,961 --> 00:52:56,001
Yes, Father.

869
00:52:57,301 --> 00:52:58,831
How is the food, Father?

870
00:52:59,231 --> 00:53:00,271
It's wonderful.

871
00:53:04,001 --> 00:53:07,511
I think this is the first time the
two of us have eaten out together.

872
00:53:07,671 --> 00:53:09,611
Yes, I'm enjoying it very much.

873
00:53:10,311 --> 00:53:13,181
Dr. Han also said we should
spend time like this often.

874
00:53:13,251 --> 00:53:14,251
Oh, really?

875
00:53:15,621 --> 00:53:20,021
Oh, and Father, I think he's going
to get the nomination this time.

876
00:53:20,221 --> 00:53:21,221
Is that so?

877
00:53:21,221 --> 00:53:23,591
So for Councilor Hwang's
wife's events...

878
00:53:23,661 --> 00:53:26,491
and volunteer activities,
I'm trying to attend them all...

879
00:53:26,561 --> 00:53:27,861
to build up some connections.

880
00:53:28,231 --> 00:53:29,731
Just don't push yourself too hard.

881
00:53:30,201 --> 00:53:31,201
Okay.

882
00:53:36,771 --> 00:53:41,211
Father, is there something
you want to tell me?

883
00:53:43,211 --> 00:53:44,211
Se Ri.

884
00:53:44,741 --> 00:53:46,181
Yes, go ahead.

885
00:53:51,481 --> 00:53:53,221
Let's get Hyun Bin married.

886
00:53:54,891 --> 00:53:56,961
- Pardon?
- I'm counting on you.

887
00:53:57,491 --> 00:53:59,531
My one remaining wish
while I'm still alive...

888
00:54:00,831 --> 00:54:01,961
is that one thing.

889
00:54:10,871 --> 00:54:13,511
What do you think?
With a proposal like this,

890
00:54:14,211 --> 00:54:16,311
don't you think
the platform will be tempted?

891
00:54:22,051 --> 00:54:23,051
CEO Gong?

892
00:54:23,751 --> 00:54:27,551
It's like a well-made gimbap,
you could say.

893
00:54:27,951 --> 00:54:29,091
Gimbap?

894
00:54:29,221 --> 00:54:31,321
Yes.
It has all the right ingredients,

895
00:54:31,391 --> 00:54:34,461
and everything looks good,
but it's a familiar taste, you know?

896
00:54:35,091 --> 00:54:36,901
There's no killer ingredient,

897
00:54:36,961 --> 00:54:39,501
nothing to really make
your mouth water.

898
00:54:40,401 --> 00:54:44,271
Oh, is this because I called
your design a rolled omelet before,

899
00:54:44,341 --> 00:54:45,741
so you're getting your revenge now,
aren't you?

900
00:54:46,611 --> 00:54:50,641
No. I'm just telling you
it's objectively lame.

901
00:54:51,081 --> 00:54:52,151
Lame?

902
00:54:52,281 --> 00:54:56,321
Yes, the differentiating point
is especially weak.

903
00:54:59,891 --> 00:55:02,491
Wipe your mouth before you talk.
You're so sloppy.

904
00:55:02,961 --> 00:55:04,661
What does it matter to you
if I'm sloppy or not?

905
00:55:04,791 --> 00:55:06,361
You have to think about the people
who have to look at you.

906
00:55:06,431 --> 00:55:07,431
Gosh, I can't stand the sight.

907
00:55:07,731 --> 00:55:08,961
If you can't stand the sight of me,

908
00:55:08,961 --> 00:55:11,001
then why did you choose me
as your business partner?

909
00:55:12,031 --> 00:55:14,601
That's because your design skills
are proven,

910
00:55:14,601 --> 00:55:15,871
you have a good reputation
in the industry,

911
00:55:15,941 --> 00:55:17,371
and designers look up to you.

912
00:55:20,511 --> 00:55:22,911
- Is that all?
- What more should there be?

913
00:55:23,281 --> 00:55:25,611
I feel like you've got some
other trick up your sleeve.

914
00:55:25,751 --> 00:55:29,021
A trick? What are you talking about?
Unbelievable.

915
00:55:29,081 --> 00:55:31,151
It is just strange. It feels like...

916
00:55:31,151 --> 00:55:33,191
the Taehan fashion division
has been moved right over here.

917
00:55:33,551 --> 00:55:36,121
The key personnel,
the design sense, the system.

918
00:55:36,761 --> 00:55:37,791
Right?

919
00:55:38,561 --> 00:55:40,231
The real purpose
of launching this brand...

920
00:55:40,291 --> 00:55:41,931
is related to Taehan Fashion,
isn't it?

921
00:55:45,631 --> 00:55:46,631
Quiet.

922
00:55:46,701 --> 00:55:49,671
I knew it, right? So you're asking
me to be the spark, is that it?

923
00:55:49,741 --> 00:55:51,941
It's a secret.
Especially from Hye Su.

924
00:55:52,171 --> 00:55:53,611
I knew it.

925
00:55:54,811 --> 00:55:59,651
But the Vice President isn't
the problem. Hwangbo Jun Hyeok is.

926
00:55:59,881 --> 00:56:02,821
Gosh, the fashion division
was sold because of him.

927
00:56:03,651 --> 00:56:05,621
That's why I'm trying
to create a diversion.

928
00:56:07,951 --> 00:56:09,991
Should I try to win him over?

929
00:56:11,421 --> 00:56:14,231
Do you think that'll work? He has
Taehan in the palm of his hand.

930
00:56:15,131 --> 00:56:16,931
What can you offer him?

931
00:56:17,601 --> 00:56:18,601
Nothing.

932
00:56:20,301 --> 00:56:21,771
- My gosh.
- What?

933
00:56:23,401 --> 00:56:24,401
What is this now?

934
00:56:31,681 --> 00:56:35,051
Father, this is the office
that Hyun Bin...

935
00:56:35,081 --> 00:56:36,781
and Dr. Gong's daughter set up.

936
00:56:37,221 --> 00:56:38,221
Is it?

937
00:56:46,931 --> 00:56:50,831
Gosh, hold this steady.
This ladder is a piece of junk.

938
00:56:50,901 --> 00:56:53,231
Are you sure it's not your legs
that are flimsy, Director Yang?

939
00:56:53,301 --> 00:56:55,641
Hey, come on. Whatever.

940
00:56:55,941 --> 00:56:57,801
Just hold it steady
and shine the light properly, okay?

941
00:56:58,641 --> 00:57:01,071
- Gosh.
- Seriously.

942
00:57:06,451 --> 00:57:07,481
There.

943
00:57:09,821 --> 00:57:11,081
What is it?

944
00:57:18,961 --> 00:57:20,461
- Oh my.
- Gosh, my back.

945
00:57:27,701 --> 00:57:30,041
- Father, I think this is it.
- Yes.

946
00:57:30,471 --> 00:57:32,111
- Oh my.
- Oh my.

947
00:57:32,341 --> 00:57:33,941
- Oh my.
- Oh my.

948
00:57:35,611 --> 00:57:36,611
What?

949
00:57:37,241 --> 00:57:39,751
You're going to
the Police Substation to be questioned?

950
00:57:40,451 --> 00:57:41,751
Don't worry.

951
00:57:42,351 --> 00:57:43,581
I can do this.

952
00:57:44,081 --> 00:57:47,091
Mom, Dae Han went to look
at an ultrasound machine.

953
00:57:47,151 --> 00:57:49,691
He said he'd be back early,
so make sure you leave work with him.

954
00:57:49,921 --> 00:57:51,521
And don't go anywhere by yourself.

955
00:57:52,291 --> 00:57:53,391
Okay.

956
00:57:54,291 --> 00:57:55,761
Be careful.

957
00:57:56,061 --> 00:57:58,301
- Okay.
- Let's go, Father.

958
00:57:58,561 --> 00:57:59,631
We'll be back.

959
00:58:05,871 --> 00:58:07,911
Sir, what's your name?

960
00:58:08,211 --> 00:58:09,211
I'm...

961
00:58:09,581 --> 00:58:11,781
My name is Gong Gi Cheol.

962
00:58:14,651 --> 00:58:15,751
I've never met...

963
00:58:16,521 --> 00:58:19,291
anyone named Jo Mun Sik.

964
00:58:19,651 --> 00:58:21,851
Then do you know Jo Mi Hyang?

965
00:58:22,261 --> 00:58:24,321
- Is she your sister?
- No.

966
00:58:24,821 --> 00:58:26,461
I don't have a younger sister.

967
00:58:26,691 --> 00:58:30,531
- Wow, your memory's coming back.
- Yes.

968
00:58:30,931 --> 00:58:34,031
Last time, you said
you committed murder yourself.

969
00:58:34,271 --> 00:58:37,641
Oh, that's what Jo Mi Hyang told me.

970
00:58:38,201 --> 00:58:41,171
That I'd killed someone
and was on the run.

971
00:58:42,941 --> 00:58:46,381
But a memory came back
to me recently.

972
00:58:46,551 --> 00:58:49,021
Bring him back to life.
Bring him back!

973
00:58:58,691 --> 00:59:03,061
Sir, is it possible that Jo Mi Hyang
killed her brother, Jo Mun Sik?

974
00:59:03,601 --> 00:59:06,231
It's possible. She tried to kill me,

975
00:59:06,301 --> 00:59:08,731
and she tried to kill
my family, too.

976
00:59:29,321 --> 00:59:32,261
She can't control her temper.

977
00:59:32,361 --> 00:59:34,891
I'm sure she's mentally ill.

978
00:59:35,561 --> 00:59:40,031
When you woke up,
you didn't see Jo Mun Sik's body?

979
00:59:40,401 --> 00:59:41,601
My head hurt so much back then,

980
00:59:41,671 --> 00:59:43,301
I was drifting in and out
of consciousness.

981
00:59:43,771 --> 00:59:47,971
Oh, then was that house
in Wolseon-dong?

982
00:59:49,381 --> 00:59:52,351
I don't know the exact location,

983
00:59:52,811 --> 00:59:55,551
but she said the police
were after me,

984
00:59:55,921 --> 00:59:57,821
so we moved right away.

985
00:59:59,091 --> 01:00:02,721
Do you know where Jo Mi Hyang
might be now?

986
01:00:04,691 --> 01:00:06,161
I don't know.

987
01:00:10,461 --> 01:00:11,461
What?

988
01:00:16,171 --> 01:00:19,371
- Oh, Dae Han.
- Mom, I'm on my way.

989
01:00:19,871 --> 01:00:22,481
Don't leave work by yourself.
Let's go together.

990
01:00:23,211 --> 01:00:24,941
Okay, got it.

991
01:00:40,861 --> 01:00:44,361
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

992
01:00:57,141 --> 01:01:00,551
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

993
01:01:40,351 --> 01:01:42,821
(Recipe For Love)

994
01:01:42,891 --> 01:01:46,991
There were red spots breaking out
on Father's skin.

995
01:01:47,061 --> 01:01:50,101
I should take him to the hospital
and get him checked out.

996
01:01:51,501 --> 01:01:56,741
From now on,
call me Stylist Yang, please.

997
01:01:58,801 --> 01:02:00,241
Yes, I'm getting off here!

998
01:02:00,311 --> 01:02:03,111
If you don't have feelings for each other,
you don't fight like that.

999
01:02:03,211 --> 01:02:05,911
If you're indifferent to each other,
you don't even talk.

1000
01:02:05,981 --> 01:02:07,451
I trust Ju Ah.

1001
01:02:07,511 --> 01:02:10,051
Well, don't be so complacent,
or you'll regret it later.

1002
01:02:10,121 --> 01:02:11,121
Hey, that's enough.

1003
01:02:11,121 --> 01:02:12,181
What?

1004
01:02:12,181 --> 01:02:14,191
Ju Ah could've been in real trouble.

1005
01:02:15,791 --> 01:02:18,061
The police are swarming
the clinic and the house,

1006
01:02:18,061 --> 01:02:19,131
but you still can't catch her?

1007
01:02:19,131 --> 01:02:21,761
What if you use me as bait?

1008
01:02:23,539 --> 01:02:25,539
Dramaday.me
